1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,240
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:19,440
<i>You called me</i>
<i>to say "sweet dreams," right?</i>

3
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,640
I know what you're trying to do.

4
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:24,200
Qin, what do you think of Duang?

5
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,280
<i>I'm worried about Qin.</i>

6
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,080
I'm worried he'd choose that person.

7
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:31,480
You even got a teddy.

8
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:32,479
From an old fling.

9
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,680
<i>I've devoted my love to him,</i>
<i>and I'll never give up.</i>

10
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:00,960
QIN VIEWED YOUR STORY

11
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:15,240
Hey!

12
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:18,360
Someone named Qin liked my Story.

13
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:20,280
Hey!

14
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:22,880
Qin liked my Story.

15
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:48,640
<i>I'm back at my place. Where are you?</i>

16
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:12,240
<i>The problem isn't Duang.</i>

17
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,320
You don't let anyone in.

18
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:19,240
So much so, I feel bad for him.

19
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:20,320
This is who I am.

20
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,960
I'm not pushing anyone away.

21
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,680
Right.

22
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:27,960
That means
you're opening up to the guy, correct?

23
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,640
Qin!

24
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,040
Are you tired? I bought you a drink.

25
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,160
<i>I danced so poorly.</i>

26
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:38,360
I mean, I tried,
but it looked like I didn't, right?

27
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,840
He really did work hard.

28
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,240
It's true, though.

29
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,800
You should be proud of him.

30
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:58,120
TWO WEEKS LATER

31
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:03,920
Hello.

32
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,720
An Americano, please.

33
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,560
Okay, coming right up.

34
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,520
I gave it to him,

35
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,960
the first puppy to ever
order an Americano while smiling.

36
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,480
I guess he doesn't need us anymore.

37
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,440
He vanished into thin air during break.

38
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:20,600
Now, he's out here smiling
and ordering a cup of coffee.

39
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,800
<i>'Cause I'm in love, and I can't help it.</i>

40
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,440
Gosh, stop it. Update us.

41
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,680
- How are things?
- I'd rather not say.

42
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:31,280
- Then shut your mouth!
- Hey!

43
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,760
Let me have my moment.

44
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,600
I want to tell you about the huge leap.

45
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,440
The huge leap?

46
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,680
- Don't tell me you're dating.
- Not yet.

47
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,880
What?

48
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,000
- So you're seeing each other more often?
- Not exactly.

49
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,320
What the hell?

50
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,200
I don't want to make Qin
feel uncomfortable.

51
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:48,960
- This is more than I expected.
- Right.

52
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,440
So what? Can you tell us now?

53
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:57,000
Here it is.
Qin has been replying to my messages.

54
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:59,280
He answers three messages a day.

55
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,840
This is so special! Take a look.

56
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,120
- WHERE ARE YOU?
- HOME

57
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,600
- GOOD LUCK.
- MM.

58
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,400
Clear as day.

59
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:18,400
Don't give me that condescending look.
I'm not done.

60
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,560
Guys, we were this close!

61
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,640
Hey.

62
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,800
Hey there.

63
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,080
Hey.

64
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,680
What song are you listening to?

65
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,920
Here.

66
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,880
I got you an Americano.

67
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,160
You liked my IG Story too?

68
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,080
Hey!

69
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,880
There!

70
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:20,120
You're being obvious.

71
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,720
How suspicious!

72
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:25,120
You're flustered, aren't you?

73
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,680
I'm also flustered.

74
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,400
You smiled!

75
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,880
I finally saw you smile!

76
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,440
Let's go practice!

77
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:45,560
I'm down for over 1,000 practices!

78
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:48,440
No, one million practices! Let's go.

79
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,640
Time to dance!

80
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,360
<i>Qin smiled at me.</i>

81
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,280
It was the first time ever.

82
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,320
Right…

83
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,280
I'm just getting started. Let me continue.

84
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:08,600
Qin.

85
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,360
Anyone who gets to date you
will be so freaking lucky.

86
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,800
Am I close to becoming your boyfriend?

87
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,280
Stop it.

88
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,840
You're annoyed?

89
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:36,200
Listen. They say that
painting or coloring something

90
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,880
can relieve stress and help us calm down.

91
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,920
So, shall we?

92
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:18,720
I'm done.

93
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:04,600
You feel me?

94
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,880
I was on a da-te with Qin.

95
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,760
What the hell is a "da-te"?

96
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,640
Spell it.

97
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,560
Why didn't you say the actual word?

98
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,760
- Yeah.
- A date.

99
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:22,840
It's not considered a date.
So I called it a da-te.

100
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,000
So detailed with your story.

101
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,440
Are you done?

102
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,400
No.

103
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,000
What's this song?

104
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,360
What is this song?

105
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,160
It's…

106
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,640
"Fa Khruem Khruem" by Scrubb.

107
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,000
What are you doing out here?

108
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,040
Well…

109
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,400
I'm here waiting for you.

110
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,440
I missed you.

111
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,840
This time, can I drive you home?

112
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:47,720
For real?

113
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:50,160
If that's the case…

114
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:55,640
can I carry your bag for you?

115
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:03,840
If that's the case…

116
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,640
wanna watch a movie with me?

117
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:14,760
But not today.

118
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,760
I got everything.

119
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:26,080
I've made a huge leap.

120
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,800
Duang, you're embarrassing us.

121
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,000
Yeah.

122
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,440
Guys.

123
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,280
Today, I'm having
dinner with Qin after class.

124
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,960
I'll also be driving him to his place.

125
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:40,000
- Then, I'll ask him to watch a movie.
- Right.

126
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,560
I've got popcorn and everything ready too.

127
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,240
Your Americano is ready!

128
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:48,920
I'm off to see Qin now!

129
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,640
Qin!

130
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,560
That'll be 60 baht.

131
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,320
Those guys are paying.

132
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,320
What?

133
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:57,920
Come on.

134
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:02,000
He's so uniquely cringe,
yet he wants to be with Qin.

135
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,120
Hey, that hurt.

136
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,160
What you looking at?

137
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,280
Why are you wearing these pants?

138
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,040
I ran out of clean clothes.

139
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,280
And you like wearing them?

140
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,680
Didn't you hear me?

141
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,200
Well…

142
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,400
Can you not wear them?

143
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,640
Are you nuts?

144
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,400
Fine.

145
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:55,800
Stop staring at my legs.

146
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,440
I'm sorry.

147
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,480
I'll stop staring.

148
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:08,320
But I'll be busy at noon,

149
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,400
helping with my friends' project.

150
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,880
No need to tell me that.

151
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:16,840
I have to. I don't want you to be lonely.

152
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,640
Stop this.

153
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,440
It's because I like you.

154
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,320
Just go away already.

155
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,600
I'll text you.

156
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:46,680
Duang!

157
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:49,120
Gam! I was just about to call.

158
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:52,160
Thanks for helping with the group project.

159
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,160
No worries, we're friends.

160
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,840
You're so sweet, you know that?

161
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:59,840
- You're always nice to everyone.
- Right.

162
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,640
Let's head inside,
so you can get ready.

163
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,680
Come and sit here.

164
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:13,800
And, Duang, this is Yim,

165
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:15,800
your modeling partner for the shoot.

166
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,040
Hi, Duang.

167
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,320
You're so handsome.

168
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,760
You also look great.

169
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:27,280
- She's actually partnering with me?
- Come on!

170
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,840
Everyone thinks you're cute.
Don't be so humble.

171
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,640
What? Me?

172
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:35,080
Gam, the way you talk…
It's not a different Duang, right?

173
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,280
Duang. It's you, the one and only.

174
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,760
Come on, time for makeup.

175
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:44,680
Sweetie, make sure
he looks nice and handsome, okay?

176
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,040
Got it?

177
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:47,880
Nook,

178
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,720
this way.

179
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,000
- Hello.
- Hi.

180
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,320
We're doing a promo shoot
for the university t-shirt.

181
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,480
I want you to look charming and bright.

182
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,320
As for you, be cool and be yourself, okay?
I'm counting on you.

183
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,440
After you're done, go get changed there.

184
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:04,440
- Sure.
- Okay.

185
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:11,680
Can I get a quick shot of you
for the student union?

186
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,960
- Sure thing!
- Okay. This background will do.

187
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,760
You're too far apart!

188
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,319
Can you guys get a bit closer?

189
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,280
There you go.

190
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:23,079
This one's a video, okay? Closer.

191
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,880
Okay, rolling.

192
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,720
Some physical contact, maybe?

193
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,440
- Physical?
- Yes, like… Yeah! Like that!

194
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,680
Make it look like you guys are close.

195
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,680
Nice and cute.

196
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:35,720
Okay.

197
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,200
I'm sorry, Duang.

198
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,600
Ready?

199
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:41,840
Make yourselves look adorable and lively.

200
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:44,440
One, two, three!

201
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:53,320
YOUR CLASS IS OVER, RIGHT?
I'M WAITING FOR YOU AT THE SAME SPOT.

202
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,560
Hey, guys. Care for some food?

203
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,120
Let's go.

204
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,160
I'm busy.

205
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,720
Qin.

206
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:06,680
Have you seen this? It's your lover boy.

207
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,320
See?

208
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,640
All you've been doing
is playing hard to get.

209
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,680
See what happened?

210
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,280
He did what he was told to.

211
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,600
Don't make it a big deal.

212
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:24,240
But you don't care about
any of this anyway, right?

213
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:33,600
It's work.

214
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:43,440
Don't tell me
you can actually get jealous? What?

215
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,760
Isn't this a surprise?

216
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:50,200
I'm gonna go.

217
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,200
- What?
- See you.

218
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,480
Already?

219
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,880
See? You showed him the post,

220
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,440
and he just left.

221
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,320
He's gone.
I bet he's going to see Duang.

222
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,640
True.

223
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:15,080
I think the lover boy has
managed to chip away at his walls.

224
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,520
Yeah.

225
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,080
Cool.

226
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,600
Is he coming?

227
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,320
- Who?
- Is Qin coming?

228
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,680
"Is he? Is he coming?"

229
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,800
Gosh, you guys are useless!

230
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:29,520
Duang!

231
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,760
Gam asked me to bring you this iPad.

232
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,240
Oh, Yim!

233
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:36,240
Thank you.
I thought Gam would bring it to me.

234
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:40,200
It's fine.
It's on the way to my building.

235
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,880
Is this your friend?

236
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:45,400
Yeah. We were modeling together.

237
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:47,240
Yim, this is Jamie,

238
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:48,320
and that's Pae.

239
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,480
Hello.

240
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:53,080
Ask her to come eat with us.

241
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:58,440
Yim, do you want to eat with us
if you're free? It's on me.

242
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:02,040
Big spender. I'd like that.

243
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,240
Duang.

244
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,480
Qin!

245
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,680
Are you hungry?

246
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:18,920
Let's go eat.

247
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,080
Garlic shrimp?

248
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,560
These guys are coming with us, though.
Is it cool with you?

249
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:27,720
Anything goes.

250
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,240
You're Qin, right?

251
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:32,480
I'm Yim.

252
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,920
Your friend is very handsome, Duang.

253
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,240
You might not remember me,

254
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:39,400
but back at Freshy Night,

255
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,320
you looked really cool.

256
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:46,560
But how do you know Duang and his friends?

257
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,680
You guys are
in different faculties, right?

258
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,120
I missed you so much!

259
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:01,560
Duang is killing it today.

260
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:04,040
He's absolutely on fire!

261
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,720
How do you want me to respond?

262
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:12,480
Anything.

263
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:15,040
I want a heartwarming response.

264
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,840
I missed you too.

265
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,640
Is that heartwarming enough?

266
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,520
This… My heart's about to burst!

267
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:50,120
You guys are really funny.

268
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,480
Since when were we trying to be funny?

269
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:02,960
Honestly, Jamie, we should tell her.

270
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:05,480
It'll be disastrous if we don't.

271
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:09,320
I know, but it'll be fine.
Let me enjoy this.

272
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,520
Shall we get going?

273
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:18,240
Let's go eat!

274
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:29,760
Thank you!

275
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,160
No need to rub it in.

276
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,360
What do we do now?

277
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:35,600
What are you waiting for?

278
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,040
Qin!

279
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:40,480
Sit with me in the back.

280
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:42,680
I really want to sit next to you.

281
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:45,080
Let me take care of your stuff.

282
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:03,840
Are you watching any good shows
or movies these days?

283
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:08,440
If you are, I'd love some recommendations.

284
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,040
I do. I want to watch<i> A Star Is Born.</i>

285
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:15,120
Qin and I
are going to watch it at his place.

286
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:18,840
However, he's been busy, so we
haven't had a chance to watch it. Right?

287
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:23,120
What's the film about?

288
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,920
It's a romantic drama film
about two singers.

289
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,160
I want to see it as well.

290
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:33,360
You definitely should.
I think it'll be good.

291
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,960
We can talk about it
after I watch it with Qin.

292
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:39,200
Will you be free soon?

293
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,800
I want to watch it with you.

294
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:45,440
I have to focus on driving now.

295
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:48,120
I can't wait to look at you face-to-face.

296
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,600
Don't miss me just yet, okay?

297
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:51,880
Eyes on the road.

298
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,480
Sure thing.

299
00:23:56,120 --> 00:24:00,360
Duang, you're so polite
when you talk to your friends.

300
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,880
I'm trying to win Qin.

301
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:04,640
Isn't that right?

302
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,440
But you're failing.

303
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,120
I'm so sorry.

304
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:14,840
Qin, I'm sorry.

305
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,960
How about we swap seats right away?

306
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:17,960
It's okay.

307
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:19,760
Seats don't matter.

308
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:27,640
I'm really sorry, Qin.

309
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,640
Sorry for what?

310
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,080
Gosh, you're so unique.

311
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,520
Just shut it.

312
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,640
Clueless!

313
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:37,680
Good grief, you're in trouble now!

314
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:39,080
Right?

315
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,320
Right?

316
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,840
Hello!

317
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,760
You're here with so…

318
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:51,560
Take a seat! So many of you.

319
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,840
Have a seat.

320
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,320
All right.

321
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:59,000
Don't look so confused!

322
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:02,760
This is your seat,
at the end of the table.

323
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,640
- Isn't this a good spot?
- Thank you, ma'am.

324
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:05,760
Isn't this nice?

325
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:10,800
What are you guys having?
The usual? Garlic shrimp?

326
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:13,040
As for you?

327
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:16,160
Gosh, you forgot already?
Basil with crispy pork belly.

328
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:17,760
I was about to say that!

329
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,720
- Make it two!
- Okay. Got it.

330
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:21,760
I'll also have garlic shrimp.

331
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,720
Sit tight.
Your food will be ready shortly.

332
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:26,800
Thank you for inviting me.

333
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:37,720
I'm so glad I'm here again.
I didn't expect you to say yes.

334
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:39,760
And,

335
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:43,000
I was so freaking excited
during the photoshoot.

336
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,360
Really?

337
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:54,160
I wasn't nervous at all
since everyone was so nice.

338
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,080
Gam and Yim, I mean.

339
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,720
Yeah, I can tell.

340
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:04,680
Hey, should we watch a movie?

341
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,640
I really wanna watch one with you.

342
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,160
Are you sleepy?

343
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,520
We can watch one later, you know?

344
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,040
Are you asleep?

345
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,480
Qin.

346
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,120
Qin.

347
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,960
Qin.

348
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,240
Qin.

349
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:45,200
What?

350
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:51,480
That's strange.

351
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,360
What's going on?

352
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:56,080
What is it?

353
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:58,560
Is he sulking? What's he upset about?

354
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,560
What is it about?

355
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:03,920
Was it about Yim apologizing?

356
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,120
Were you jealous over me?

357
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,880
Nothing's going on with Yim.
We just met at the photoshoot.

358
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:16,120
And I only invited her to a meal
because I wanted to thank her

359
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:19,280
for returning my iPad.
I forgot it earlier.

360
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:21,040
Please don't be upset with me.

361
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,280
Fine.

362
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:33,840
How are you feeling right now?

363
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:40,400
Yim's pretty cute. She'd be good for you.

364
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:45,160
Don't say that. Let's make up.

365
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:46,680
Let's make up.

366
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:47,640
Let's make up.

367
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,880
Make up for what? I'm not mad.

368
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:58,840
Where are you going?

369
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:01,880
Bathroom.

370
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:06,440
Okay, don't take too long.

371
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:09,200
I'll make popcorn. Hurry back, okay?

372
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:47,320
You're so freaking cute, that it hurts.

373
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:05,680
Are you over the thing with Yim and me?

374
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:12,040
Are we gonna watch the movie?
Let's finish it, so you can go.

375
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Let's watch then.

376
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,960
You didn't wash your face properly.

377
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,120
Stop talking in that tone.

378
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:28,080
Just say it if you like it.

379
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:30,800
No one else is here,
so what's with the act?

380
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:34,400
It's not like that.

381
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:36,520
So what is it?

382
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:02,200
Isn't that too close?

383
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,920
Oh, you!

384
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,880
Don't speak like that often.

385
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:14,000
Why? Are you saying
it makes your heart race?

386
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,680
Am I right?

387
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:22,040
If you admit it,
I'll only use that tone sometimes.

388
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,120
You're so cute.

389
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,320
Shut up.

390
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,320
You're so freaking cute.

391
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,560
You're the cutest.

392
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,520
<i>Shall we clink our glasses together?</i>

393
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,400
What's your name?

394
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:09,640
It's Mar.

395
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:15,080
What?

396
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:19,880
Hey.

397
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:21,640
Is he alive?

398
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:25,200
He's alive.

399
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,400
What was that?

400
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:32,040
I thought it was a mosquito.
What's up with you?

401
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:37,440
What? Just spit it out.
Why are you zoning out?

402
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,240
It's hard to explain.

403
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:42,600
All right, whatever.

404
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:45,800
Wait! Sit down.

405
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:46,960
You fucking bastard.

406
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,840
Why did you call me that?

407
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:50,520
My heart is only this tiny.

408
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,160
Hey, for real. What's going on?

409
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:54,600
Don't force me!

410
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,520
I'm out.

411
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,760
Pae…

412
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:59,200
Can you just listen?

413
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:02,240
If you mess around with me one more time,

414
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:05,520
I'll take that ice
and throw it in your face.

415
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:10,200
You got nothing good to say to me.
Who taught you to talk like that?

416
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,280
Fine.

417
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:20,040
I've been waiting for someone

418
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:22,440
at the same place and time.

419
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:26,520
I don't remember how many nights I waited,
but they never came.

420
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,680
Hey!

421
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:31,760
Are we losing a player
to the lover boy squad?

422
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:34,400
Lover boy, my ass. Not in my book.

423
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:37,760
I won't lose my heart to a game

424
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:41,560
'cause players never fall in love.

425
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:44,240
That was so fucking dramatic.

426
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,120
I can't even spell the damn word.

427
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:50,400
Does it start with an L or an R? R…

428
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:54,240
You can't spell
because you're a dumbass, Jettana.

429
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,800
We're late.

430
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:06,320
Let's get to class,
so you can sharpen your skills for once.

431
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,520
Prachai, did you ever love me--

432
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,160
You're making me sad.

433
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:16,120
- Stop acting and go to class.
- Come back to me!

434
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,080
Do you know that

435
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:25,720
skeletons of different ages
look different?

436
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:32,040
The same goes for different genders.

437
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,520
Now…

438
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:36,400
What's wrong with you, Duang?

439
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:40,040
When I watched a movie with Qin yesterday,

440
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,920
he kinda acted jealous of Yim and me.

441
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,000
That's when you realized?

442
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:50,840
Part of me worried he might overthink it,
but another part of me was like,

443
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:53,440
"Shit, that means he has feelings for me."

444
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:59,040
Today's practice is gonna be so awkward!

445
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:02,480
Isn't it too late to be awkward?

446
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,800
You've been through
practice after practice,

447
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,360
Lover boy of Nakhon Pathom.

448
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,280
Top dog, second to none.

449
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,719
You're all alone on the podium!

450
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:13,880
Right, Duang.

451
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:17,600
Don't forget our meeting tonight
after practice.

452
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:20,199
Hey. Did you even hear what I said?

453
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,639
Duang.

454
00:34:21,719 --> 00:34:24,320
And did you hear what I said, Jettana?

455
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:27,159
Yes, Professor.

456
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:29,040
Have you ever paid attention to me?

457
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:31,880
- I'm listening, sir.
- You think you're so smart?

458
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:34,960
Stand up and answer my question.

459
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:37,480
How about this? If you get this right,

460
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,360
everyone can go home.

461
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:40,560
The class will be over.

462
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:45,840
The question is,

463
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:48,560
what is the motto of Phrae province?

464
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:50,440
Jeez, Professor.

465
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:54,440
Who could even answer that?
We're all from Nakhon Pathom.

466
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,120
The knowledgeable one could.

467
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:58,520
"Mo hom fabric and teak wood.
Place of Phra Lo's love.

468
00:34:58,600 --> 00:34:59,800
Home of Cho Hae.

469
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,040
Famed Phae Mueang Phi.

470
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:02,960
The generous people of Phrae."

471
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:15,120
Jettana, are you from Phrae?

472
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:16,360
No, I'm not.

473
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:18,720
Shit, you're clever.

474
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:23,240
I'm Jettana, the Encyclopedia.

475
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:30,920
Professor, don't forget your promise.

476
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,880
I keep my promises.

477
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:39,760
I'm a man of my word.

478
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,160
Fine, class is over, you suckers!

479
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:49,000
- "Famed Phae Mueang Phi!"
- Shit, you're awesome!

480
00:35:50,720 --> 00:35:52,440
See you later.

481
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,120
Bye, the Encyclopedia.

482
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:01,240
Not a dictionary, it's an encyclopedia!

483
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:08,280
One, two…

484
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,800
- One…
- Swoosh.

485
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:22,880
- Touch.
- Touch.

486
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,040
- Step.
- Touch.

487
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:30,080
Yay!

488
00:36:31,160 --> 00:36:32,720
My boys are growing up!

489
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:33,640
True.

490
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:36,120
You guys are doing amazing,

491
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:38,800
especially when you dance.

492
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:42,000
Duang, you keep getting better and better.

493
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:45,560
Hey, your making me blush, Alice.

494
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:47,240
I gotta give all the credits to Qin.

495
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:49,880
With an instructor like Qin,
anyone would have crushed it.

496
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:56,120
I asked a senior to do the choreography,
but Duang worked hard too.

497
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:57,960
I see.

498
00:36:58,040 --> 00:37:01,960
Wait, I'm sensing some chemistry here.

499
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:03,440
Is there anything I should know?

500
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:06,160
Well, silly you!

501
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:08,600
Alice, what could there be?

502
00:37:08,680 --> 00:37:10,360
- There's none.
- Right, there's none.

503
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,360
I think I'm losing it.

504
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:16,520
Right, are we done?
If we are, I'll head out.

505
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:17,920
Yeah, go ahead.

506
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:23,000
Excuse me, Alice.

507
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,000
- Bye, Tinn.
- All right.

508
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:35,280
Hey. Do you wanna
go grab something to eat?

509
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:37,560
I already have plans.

510
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,960
With your friends, right?

511
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,240
I almost had a heart attack.

512
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:52,320
Do you mind if I ask where?

513
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:55,360
I'd say I do mind.

514
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,840
Please tell me.

515
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:02,960
A bar near the university.

516
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,520
I'm going there myself.

517
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:08,000
X's bar, right?

518
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:10,680
Yes.

519
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:12,320
- Do you want me--
- No need.

520
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,960
My friends are picking me up.

521
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:23,360
We can just go there together
since we're going to the same place.

522
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,160
It's more economical that way.

523
00:38:25,240 --> 00:38:26,680
Why can't we?

524
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:31,080
Then I'll just walk you downstairs.

525
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:33,920
No need. And don't follow me.

526
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:41,320
How will I get out of here then?

527
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:04,240
Hello, Funan. What's up?

528
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:06,600
<i>Right, what are you up to?</i>

529
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:07,680
Dance practice?

530
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,480
<i>That's done for the day. What's up?</i>

531
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:13,640
You've been practicing for ages.
When is your show?

532
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,400
Pretty soon. Are you gonna come watch?

533
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:17,800
<i>Can I?</i>

534
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:19,920
Dad asked you to come.

535
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:22,720
- Gosh, Mr. Know-It-All.
<i>- All right.</i>

536
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:25,920
I'll keep you posted. Anything else?

537
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:29,080
Nope. Right, how's my place?

538
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:32,640
Your place is spotless.
If that's all, I'll hang up.

539
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,400
<i>All right.</i>

540
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:02,760
You good?

541
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,560
I'm fine. I just wanted to come.

542
00:40:08,960 --> 00:40:12,120
Do you wanna be here,
or do you wanna get drunk?

543
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,440
Hold up.

544
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,440
Is this a matter of the heart?

545
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,120
What did Duang do?

546
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:29,160
Nothing.

547
00:40:30,680 --> 00:40:32,640
What? So what's up with you?

548
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:38,000
All right, let's cheers.

549
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:39,360
- Let's go.
- Come on.

550
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,560
- Come on.
- Cheers.

551
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:04,120
Thank you for coming.

552
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,520
You're here, Smile?

553
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:20,680
- Happy birthday, buddy.
- Thank you.

554
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:22,720
Took you long enough.
Come. Take a seat.

555
00:41:22,800 --> 00:41:23,920
Come sit here.

556
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,360
- Yo.
- Come on.

557
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:27,040
What's up?

558
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,920
How are things at your shop?

559
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,000
I'm sorry. I had a ton of customers.

560
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:35,480
- It's fine.
- That's why I'm late.

561
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:36,640
- You're here now.
- Right.

562
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:38,800
- X! Hello!
- Hi.

563
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:42,080
Smile!

564
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:44,920
My fraternity bro! I've missed you.
Give me a hug!

565
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:46,960
You guys, get away from me.

566
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:50,720
Come and take a seat.

567
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:52,200
Here.

568
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:54,680
- Ready?
- Come on.

569
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:56,840
- Cheers!
- All right.

570
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:58,760
- Thank you so much, guys
- Right.

571
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:00,520
Cheers!

572
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:01,800
Thank you.

573
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:08,240
Who are you looking for?

574
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:10,800
That's Qin.

575
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:16,360
You're not going to say hi to him?

576
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:19,160
No, he's with his friends.

577
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:22,160
Since when did you
start caring about that?

578
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:26,480
He said he'd be at the same bar as me,
but wouldn't let me take him.

579
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:30,160
In a way, he told me to stay away.
It's like he was pushing me away.

580
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,960
You get upset too easily.

581
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:34,560
What are you guys talking about?

582
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:38,080
It's about someone
Duang is trying to win over.

583
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,880
Really? Who is it?

584
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:43,440
See those three guys
sitting at the counter?

585
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,320
The one in the white.

586
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:46,560
- There.
- Yeah.

587
00:42:46,640 --> 00:42:47,640
Why? He likes him?

588
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:53,360
What?

589
00:42:53,440 --> 00:42:55,760
It's nothing.

590
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:56,800
Where are you going?

591
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:58,800
Answering a phone call.

592
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:09,360
Duang.

593
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:12,160
- Gam?
- Hi.

594
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:17,640
My friend in the white top
has a crush on you.

595
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,280
Three of them are wearing white.

596
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:30,120
Ying!

597
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:37,320
You're single, right?

598
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:39,280
Can you give her your contact info?

599
00:43:46,760 --> 00:43:49,400
I'm sorry, Gam, but I like someone else.

600
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:55,560
It's fine.

601
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:56,760
- I'll see you later.
- Okay.

602
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:58,040
I'll go cheer her up.

603
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:02,320
I'm also single, by the way.

604
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:03,640
- Sheesh.
- My buddy's single.

605
00:44:04,200 --> 00:44:06,200
Come on. It's dangerous around here.

606
00:44:08,760 --> 00:44:10,240
Where's Qin?

607
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,400
His friends are still there.

608
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,800
So he's probably still here.
Maybe he's in the bathroom.

609
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:20,080
I'll be right back then.

610
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:23,040
I'll be back, guys. Give me a moment.

611
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:36,680
- Hey!
- Back off.

612
00:44:46,120 --> 00:44:47,400
Are you all right?

613
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:56,760
I don't want to talk to you.

614
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:42,520
- All right, let's make a toast.
- Let's.

615
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:44,560
- Jamie, come on.
- Let's go.

616
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:46,560
- Cheers.
- Bottoms up.

617
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:47,880
Easy.

618
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:53,680
- Are you drunk?
- No, I'm not.

619
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:55,880
- Come on. Keep 'em coming.
- One more.

620
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:02,760
Come on, one more!

621
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:04,320
- One more!
- I've had enough.

622
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,760
I want to draw something.

623
00:46:05,840 --> 00:46:08,280
- Do you have a pen?
- Of course I do.

624
00:46:08,360 --> 00:46:10,200
- What are you doing?
- A sketch.

625
00:46:10,280 --> 00:46:12,040
- A sketch?
- Right now?

626
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,560
- What's gotten into you?
- Of what?

627
00:46:15,040 --> 00:46:16,160
I don't know.

628
00:46:17,120 --> 00:46:20,080
I'm making a sketch
of the sun and the moon.

629
00:46:20,160 --> 00:46:21,600
The sun and the moon?

630
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:26,400
You can still sketch?

631
00:46:27,560 --> 00:46:29,200
He's in one of his moods.

632
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:33,400
Check it out. It's done!

633
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:36,560
Hey, this is beautiful.
Come on, take a look.

634
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:37,880
What do you think?

635
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:39,800
I'm a man who studies Decorative Arts,

636
00:46:40,360 --> 00:46:41,880
and so did you guys, right?

637
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:43,040
You're still a kid.

638
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:46,440
Why shoot me down?

639
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:47,880
- Right.
- Let me take a photo.

640
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:49,680
Here you go. Take a photo of me?

641
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,600
No, the paper towel.

642
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:58,640
Three, two… Cheese!

643
00:46:58,720 --> 00:47:00,640
There you go.

644
00:47:00,720 --> 00:47:02,160
Let me see that again.

645
00:47:04,560 --> 00:47:06,040
Not bad for being drunk.

646
00:47:06,120 --> 00:47:07,080
- Right?
- Yeah.

647
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:10,800
Do you want to get a tattoo of this?

648
00:47:12,640 --> 00:47:14,400
Yeah! Get a tattoo.

649
00:47:14,480 --> 00:47:15,440
He runs a tattoo shop.

650
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:17,400
- Do it.
- No, I'd rather not.

651
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:19,120
- What?
- Want a tattoo?

652
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:22,240
- Don't chicken out.
- Come on, don't.

653
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:23,360
Sheesh.

654
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,760
I'm not chickening out.

655
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:28,960
Here's the deal.

656
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:31,320
I usually charge 4,000 baht per tattoo.

657
00:47:31,800 --> 00:47:33,760
I'll give you two tattoos for 3,200 baht.

658
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:37,040
- Interested?
- This is a steal at this rate.

659
00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:38,120
You can't say no.

660
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:40,320
- Yeah.
- Do it.

661
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:43,240
- Guys, let's not.
- Why?

662
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:44,680
He's just one massive chicken.

663
00:47:45,240 --> 00:47:47,000
I'd better tell my friends at uni.

664
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:49,240
Duang's a chicken.
He's too weak to get a tattoo.

665
00:47:49,320 --> 00:47:51,320
- Sheesh.
- Yeah.

666
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:53,080
I'm down! It's just a tattoo.

667
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:54,160
I'll pay in advance too.

668
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:55,680
See you tomorrow at noon.

669
00:47:55,760 --> 00:47:57,080
Hell ya!

670
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:58,080
- Seriously?
- Are you?

671
00:47:58,160 --> 00:47:59,320
- Yes, I am.
- Perfect.

672
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:03,000
There you go! A real man pays up!

673
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:04,400
Here we go!

674
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:07,040
He's actually serious.

675
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:08,920
He's doing it for real.

676
00:48:11,400 --> 00:48:12,760
He's doing it for real.

677
00:48:12,840 --> 00:48:14,520
He actually paid him.

678
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:16,240
- Wanna to get tattoo?
- He paid.

679
00:48:21,960 --> 00:48:23,520
- Why the long face?
- Come on, kiddo.

680
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:24,760
Drink up.

681
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:26,120
- Let's keep it going.
- Okay.

682
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:27,440
Kiddo, are you good?

683
00:48:27,520 --> 00:48:28,480
Hey, come on.

684
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:35,760
Where have you been?

685
00:48:37,200 --> 00:48:38,520
Everyone's gone?

686
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:39,840
Obviously!

687
00:48:39,920 --> 00:48:41,360
You've been gone for ages.

688
00:48:41,440 --> 00:48:42,920
It was just a quick visit.

689
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:44,840
Sheesh!

690
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:49,040
The state he's in…

691
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:51,320
What should we do with him?

692
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:55,040
Duang!

693
00:48:55,840 --> 00:48:57,760
Qin.

694
00:48:58,320 --> 00:48:59,640
Qin!

695
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:01,680
Qin.

696
00:49:01,760 --> 00:49:04,640
- Hey. I've got an idea.
- What is it?

697
00:49:06,560 --> 00:49:08,080
Take Duang to Qin's place.

698
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:10,400
Hey!

699
00:49:13,040 --> 00:49:14,240
You're such a genius.

700
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:15,520
- You carry him.
- What?

701
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:16,720
Come on, help me out!

702
00:49:16,800 --> 00:49:17,640
Gosh.

703
00:49:18,440 --> 00:49:20,480
His face is about to hit the floor.

704
00:49:21,800 --> 00:49:23,000
Hold him, come on!

705
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:26,680
What?

706
00:49:30,120 --> 00:49:31,720
He's so heavy.

707
00:49:34,360 --> 00:49:35,200
Qin…

708
00:49:35,280 --> 00:49:37,560
Where does Qin live? Duang, do you know?

709
00:49:37,640 --> 00:49:39,880
I do. I'll show you the way.

710
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:42,440
One, three, four, five.

711
00:49:42,520 --> 00:49:44,160
- One, three…
- How cool is this?

712
00:49:44,240 --> 00:49:46,800
He's completely hammered,
but he got us here.

713
00:49:47,600 --> 00:49:49,160
This is it!

714
00:50:05,760 --> 00:50:09,480
The guard recognized Duang,
so he let us in.

715
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:11,040
I'm sorry, Qin.

716
00:50:11,120 --> 00:50:14,160
Duang refused to tell us
where his keycard is.

717
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:17,800
And we couldn't find it.
Can we drop him off here?

718
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:21,240
I'm staying with my partner,

719
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:23,280
so I can't bring him to my place.

720
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:25,520
What about you, Jamie?

721
00:50:26,320 --> 00:50:28,480
This warrior has to go to war.

722
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:30,320
The night isn't over for me, Qin.

723
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:32,440
- Please take him.
- Please take him.

724
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:34,840
Hey, Duang.

725
00:50:36,320 --> 00:50:37,320
You're here.

726
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:41,760
Qin!

727
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:46,040
Are you the real Qin?

728
00:50:46,120 --> 00:50:49,040
If he crosses the line,
feel free to smack him.

729
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:52,200
Why are you so adorable?

730
00:50:52,960 --> 00:50:54,640
Are you the real one?

731
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:56,640
Are you?

732
00:51:12,640 --> 00:51:13,880
If it weren't for us,

733
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:16,840
he'd have to wait until his next life
to stay over at Qin's.

734
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:20,360
Wait, Jamie.
Duang's room doesn't need a keycard.

735
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:25,920
Come on, it was fine.
It worked out, didn't it?

736
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:29,040
- Let's go.
- How did you go from stupid to smart?

737
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:30,840
- What?
- Nothing.

738
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:50,120
Hey.

739
00:53:36,920 --> 00:53:38,520
You're looking at me?

740
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:45,760
I'm thinking about what to do with you.

741
00:53:49,960 --> 00:53:51,560
Why are you mad at me?

742
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:54,000
Can you please tell me?

743
00:53:58,320 --> 00:53:59,560
I won't do it again.

744
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:05,800
Not now. You're drunk.

745
00:54:15,160 --> 00:54:16,720
I've sobered up.

746
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:26,560
I'm actually not mad at you.

747
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:29,280
You didn't do anything wrong.

748
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:33,920
I simply…

749
00:54:35,760 --> 00:54:37,960
don't like it when
I can't control my emotions.

750
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:42,120
I love it when I've got nobody by my side.

751
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:44,280
It's stable, safe…

752
00:54:45,320 --> 00:54:47,960
and there's not much to think about.

753
00:54:58,120 --> 00:54:59,560
It's because of me, isn't it?

754
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:01,240
Yes.

755
00:55:04,640 --> 00:55:06,160
I won't do it again.

756
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:31,360
You've done nothing, so why say that?

757
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:40,680
What did you say?

758
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:45,560
Nothing.

759
00:55:52,760 --> 00:55:53,760
I think…

760
00:55:55,080 --> 00:55:56,640
I'm going to take a shower.

761
00:55:57,960 --> 00:55:58,960
I have a headache.

762
00:56:05,360 --> 00:56:06,840
You don't say.

763
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:08,880
You were drinking like a fool.

764
00:56:10,240 --> 00:56:11,360
So harsh.

765
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:14,080
Go shower already.

766
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:16,080
So you can go to bed.

767
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:26,000
I still love you when you're harsh.

768
00:56:30,720 --> 00:56:31,600
Get going.

769
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:55,880
Hey!

770
00:57:11,320 --> 00:57:13,160
I'm not wearing any underwear.

771
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:22,080
That hurt!

772
00:57:22,640 --> 00:57:23,920
By the way,

773
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:26,800
we look like the characters
from <i>Bananas in Pyjamas.</i>

774
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,520
Hello, B1.

775
00:57:30,760 --> 00:57:32,480
You've sobered up, B2?

776
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:34,160
Do you want to go home then?

777
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:39,320
I still can't walk straight.

778
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:54,800
Qin.

779
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:12,920
I'm not drunk, by the way.

780
00:58:16,360 --> 00:58:17,720
I like you.

781
00:58:19,880 --> 00:58:22,280
My feelings are
still the same as on the first day.

782
00:58:23,080 --> 00:58:25,600
I'm not here to pressure you.

783
00:58:26,080 --> 00:58:29,400
I just want you to know that
nothing has changed.

784
00:58:32,160 --> 00:58:35,600
I'm prepared to love you
with everything I have.

785
00:59:40,440 --> 00:59:42,040
Hey, you.

786
01:00:12,040 --> 01:00:14,120
That hurt!

787
01:00:15,280 --> 01:00:17,840
My bad. I was caught off guard.

788
01:00:18,320 --> 01:00:19,880
Took you a while.

789
01:00:19,960 --> 01:00:21,880
Those were some mad blows.

790
01:00:23,720 --> 01:00:25,040
It's fine. Since you're awake,

791
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:27,400
I was thinking we could cuddle
and sleep a bit more.

792
01:00:27,480 --> 01:00:28,560
Please?

793
01:00:29,800 --> 01:00:30,920
Hey!

794
01:00:37,680 --> 01:00:40,880
We don't have dance practice today.
Since we're free, should we go out?

795
01:00:42,080 --> 01:00:45,080
Like, we can go on a date or something.

796
01:00:45,640 --> 01:00:46,560
Who says I'm free?

797
01:00:47,760 --> 01:00:49,160
I have plans.

798
01:00:53,920 --> 01:00:55,080
Wanna come with?

799
01:00:56,040 --> 01:00:56,880
Yes!

800
01:00:56,960 --> 01:00:58,640
I wanna come with!

801
01:01:04,720 --> 01:01:05,960
You!

802
01:01:11,400 --> 01:01:14,040
Qin asked me out!

803
01:01:19,720 --> 01:01:21,920
FIRE TIGER RAMEN

804
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:25,080
Hey, wanna grab a bite first?

805
01:01:25,160 --> 01:01:26,840
No, we're gonna be late.

806
01:01:27,320 --> 01:01:28,640
For what?

807
01:01:28,720 --> 01:01:31,240
I thought you were shopping.
Or are you meeting someone?

808
01:01:32,520 --> 01:01:34,400
I'm not meeting anyone. You are.

809
01:01:39,680 --> 01:01:40,960
I'm down! It's just a tattoo.

810
01:01:41,040 --> 01:01:42,080
I'll pay in advance too.

811
01:01:42,160 --> 01:01:43,560
See you tomorrow at noon.

812
01:01:43,640 --> 01:01:44,520
There you go!

813
01:01:44,600 --> 01:01:46,240
A real man pays up!

814
01:01:47,880 --> 01:01:48,880
Holy shit.

815
01:01:49,720 --> 01:01:51,160
You knew about that?

816
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:52,520
The whole bar heard.

817
01:01:53,480 --> 01:01:55,200
Show-offs gotta show up.

818
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:57,560
Oh, man!

819
01:01:57,640 --> 01:01:59,720
I can just skip it. It wasn't much.

820
01:02:00,560 --> 01:02:01,520
It's still money.

821
01:02:01,600 --> 01:02:04,800
Can I not go? I'm afraid of needles!

822
01:02:05,520 --> 01:02:06,360
Come on.

823
01:02:06,440 --> 01:02:07,440
Hey!

824
01:02:15,160 --> 01:02:16,960
How do you know about this place?

825
01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:24,960
I confirmed two designs.

826
01:02:26,400 --> 01:02:27,320
So?

827
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:29,880
I can just do one, right?

828
01:02:31,000 --> 01:02:33,200
It's such a shame
the other one is so pretty.

829
01:02:41,760 --> 01:02:44,000
- I'm just showing you, not asking--
- I'll do it.

830
01:02:46,760 --> 01:02:48,480
I'm not forcing you or anything.

831
01:02:49,280 --> 01:02:50,800
You can't force me.

832
01:02:54,960 --> 01:02:58,760
You're really here.
Thought you'd chicken out.

833
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:01,600
Jeez, bro. I already paid.

834
01:03:01,680 --> 01:03:04,960
Don't want to waste your money?
Are you each getting one?

835
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:09,720
You actually managed
to find someone else, huh?

836
01:03:09,800 --> 01:03:11,200
All right, where do you want it?

837
01:03:11,280 --> 01:03:13,920
Inner ankle, please. What about you, Qin?

838
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:15,520
Left ankle, please.

839
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:19,200
Then I'm gonna do mine on my right ankle.

840
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:26,040
Okay, great.
Excuse me while I prepare the equipment.

841
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:33,520
Hey, you.

842
01:03:34,200 --> 01:03:36,920
Hey. I think I'll pass out for sure.

843
01:03:38,120 --> 01:03:40,280
It's not gonna hurt.
Just like a car crash.

844
01:03:41,560 --> 01:03:43,000
How does that not hurt?

845
01:03:43,080 --> 01:03:45,760
I read about it. Ankles don't hurt.

846
01:03:46,360 --> 01:03:47,520
Really?

847
01:03:48,080 --> 01:03:48,920
Yeah.

848
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:51,000
Did you do any research?

849
01:03:51,920 --> 01:03:53,240
I'm sorry.

850
01:03:55,720 --> 01:03:57,960
Should I go first since you're so scared?

851
01:03:58,040 --> 01:04:02,400
Not a chance. I wanna go first.
If it's too much, you won't have to do it.

852
01:04:16,200 --> 01:04:17,480
Is it gonna hurt?

853
01:04:18,560 --> 01:04:21,600
Not too much. Easy.

854
01:04:22,920 --> 01:04:23,760
Ready?

855
01:04:25,720 --> 01:04:28,240
- I am.
- Okay.

856
01:04:28,840 --> 01:04:29,840
Here we go.

857
01:04:34,080 --> 01:04:35,280
- I haven't started.
- Right.

858
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:39,320
Three, two…

859
01:04:46,120 --> 01:04:47,360
Wanna hold it?

860
01:05:01,160 --> 01:05:02,480
Hold still.

861
01:05:03,520 --> 01:05:04,560
That hurts.

862
01:05:04,640 --> 01:05:07,040
No shit, it's a tattoo.
Of course it hurts.

863
01:05:08,160 --> 01:05:10,400
Here comes the color.
It will hurt a little.

864
01:05:11,360 --> 01:05:12,800
Is it gonna hurt a lot?

865
01:05:12,880 --> 01:05:14,240
A little more than earlier.

866
01:05:14,320 --> 01:05:15,320
Like an ant bite?

867
01:05:15,400 --> 01:05:16,240
Like a colony.

868
01:05:25,080 --> 01:05:26,400
Almost done.

869
01:05:28,240 --> 01:05:31,680
Just a little more.

870
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:37,240
Done.

871
01:05:40,800 --> 01:05:41,800
There you go.

872
01:05:47,120 --> 01:05:48,520
That's pretty.

873
01:05:48,600 --> 01:05:50,080
Here. Let me wipe it clean.

874
01:05:51,120 --> 01:05:52,400
The sun looks good on you.

875
01:05:59,640 --> 01:06:03,080
Come on. Let me cover it up.

876
01:06:05,760 --> 01:06:09,840
And don't get it wet for about a day.

877
01:06:09,920 --> 01:06:11,160
Okay.

878
01:06:11,240 --> 01:06:13,240
What do you say, Qin? Ready for yours?

879
01:06:13,320 --> 01:06:14,360
Sure.

880
01:06:19,560 --> 01:06:21,160
I can feel it.

881
01:06:21,960 --> 01:06:23,920
Ouch, Smile, slow down!

882
01:06:29,640 --> 01:06:30,880
Qin, does it hurt?

883
01:06:30,960 --> 01:06:31,920
No.

884
01:06:33,440 --> 01:06:36,480
- How do you feel, Qin? Still good?
- I'm fine.

885
01:06:36,560 --> 01:06:38,520
See? He doesn't even feel it.

886
01:06:40,720 --> 01:06:43,560
No way. I'm sure he can feel it too.

887
01:06:43,640 --> 01:06:45,560
- How do you know that?
- Smile! Be gentle!

888
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:48,320
Just a little bit more.

889
01:06:52,640 --> 01:06:53,680
Excuse me, Qin.

890
01:06:53,760 --> 01:06:55,600
You get up. Let him back on the bed.

891
01:06:57,080 --> 01:07:00,040
- Why are you whining?
- It just hurts thinking he's in pain.

892
01:07:00,120 --> 01:07:01,000
Okay then.

893
01:07:01,080 --> 01:07:02,200
You're worried, huh?

894
01:07:02,280 --> 01:07:05,600
- Or is this your ankle?
- It's Qin's.

895
01:07:16,400 --> 01:07:18,720
Did it hurt?

896
01:07:20,760 --> 01:07:21,680
What?

897
01:07:22,320 --> 01:07:23,640
Why are you guys here?

898
01:07:27,760 --> 01:07:30,040
You're the ones who told Qin
where the shop is!

899
01:07:30,840 --> 01:07:31,800
What?

900
01:07:31,880 --> 01:07:34,320
You're nuts. I never told him it was here.

901
01:07:34,400 --> 01:07:36,480
- Was it you?
- Bro, what?

902
01:07:36,560 --> 01:07:37,880
Are you done?

903
01:07:38,680 --> 01:07:40,000
That's right, I am.

904
01:07:40,080 --> 01:07:41,480
Damn, that sucks.

905
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:44,840
We came to watch you get tattooed.
Did you get both designs?

906
01:07:44,920 --> 01:07:47,960
Both designs, my ass.
Qin got one of them.

907
01:07:50,440 --> 01:07:51,720
Noob.

908
01:07:51,800 --> 01:07:54,040
Don't get me started.

909
01:07:54,120 --> 01:07:56,120
It was like being slashed by a knife!

910
01:07:58,520 --> 01:07:59,840
Was it that bad, Qin?

911
01:07:59,920 --> 01:08:01,640
Or is he just being extra?

912
01:08:02,120 --> 01:08:03,040
It didn't really hurt.

913
01:08:03,120 --> 01:08:06,400
Yikes! What a noob.

914
01:08:07,440 --> 01:08:08,480
Hey, fam.

915
01:08:08,560 --> 01:08:09,840
- The whole squad is here.
- Hi.

916
01:08:09,920 --> 01:08:11,120
Hi, there.

917
01:08:11,200 --> 01:08:13,000
Want a tattoo? I'll design one for you.

918
01:08:13,080 --> 01:08:15,840
I have to pass. My mom won't let me.

919
01:08:15,920 --> 01:08:16,960
What about you, Jamie?

920
01:08:17,520 --> 01:08:20,439
Let me think about it.
It's permanent, man.

921
01:08:20,520 --> 01:08:21,880
I think to think a lot.

922
01:08:21,960 --> 01:08:24,800
Enough with the excuses.
You're just a chicken, Jettana.

923
01:08:24,880 --> 01:08:25,960
You too, Prachai.

924
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:27,439
What?

925
01:08:27,520 --> 01:08:30,439
I just really love my mom,
unlike you, chicken.

926
01:08:31,240 --> 01:08:33,800
Yeah, at least I'm not you,
a drunk show-off.

927
01:08:33,880 --> 01:08:34,800
In your face, sucker!

928
01:08:36,279 --> 01:08:37,279
How about this?

929
01:08:37,359 --> 01:08:38,600
To prove you're not chickens,

930
01:08:38,680 --> 01:08:40,160
I'll do it for free.

931
01:08:40,240 --> 01:08:41,560
That's a steal.

932
01:08:45,240 --> 01:08:46,240
Mommy?

933
01:08:46,880 --> 01:08:48,040
Have you eaten?

934
01:08:49,760 --> 01:08:50,760
Papa!

935
01:08:51,279 --> 01:08:52,600
I miss you!

936
01:08:52,680 --> 01:08:54,680
What a bunch of chickens.

937
01:08:54,760 --> 01:08:58,040
Unlike me, who's as strong as a dog!

938
01:09:00,439 --> 01:09:01,399
A whiny one, sure.

939
01:09:02,720 --> 01:09:04,200
Whining like a dog.

940
01:09:04,279 --> 01:09:05,640
- Thank you, Smile. Bye.
- Bye.

941
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:06,640
Smile.

942
01:09:07,439 --> 01:09:08,319
See ya.

943
01:09:11,399 --> 01:09:12,720
Go home!

944
01:09:21,560 --> 01:09:23,880
Why are you taking me back to your place?

945
01:09:23,960 --> 01:09:25,200
Got something planned?

946
01:09:26,800 --> 01:09:29,200
I have parents, you know?

947
01:09:32,000 --> 01:09:33,319
Go home then.

948
01:09:33,399 --> 01:09:36,000
But my parents told me,

949
01:09:36,080 --> 01:09:37,520
"If you love someone,

950
01:09:37,600 --> 01:09:39,479
try spending the night
in their room first."

951
01:09:39,560 --> 01:09:43,040
I brought you here because it's late.
If you wanna go, be my guest.

952
01:09:43,600 --> 01:09:46,160
No way! I'm staying.

953
01:09:49,200 --> 01:09:50,680
Then I'll take a shower.

954
01:09:51,319 --> 01:09:52,880
Do you need a hand?

955
01:09:58,400 --> 01:09:59,280
Sure.

956
01:10:07,640 --> 01:10:09,280
Don't do this to me.

957
01:10:10,880 --> 01:10:13,200
I could literally die.

958
01:10:33,280 --> 01:10:36,000
You haven't even won me over.
Are you really dying?

959
01:10:56,560 --> 01:10:58,200
I'd better hurry then.

960
01:11:39,960 --> 01:11:41,160
That's Qin! He's here!

961
01:11:41,240 --> 01:11:43,080
Qin is here!

962
01:11:43,640 --> 01:11:45,320
I want to practice dance.

963
01:11:45,400 --> 01:11:47,280
<i>I've dedicated</i>
<i>too much time to basketball.</i>

964
01:11:48,480 --> 01:11:50,040
Shaking in your boots?

965
01:11:51,200 --> 01:11:53,560
Will you be mad at me if I fail miserably?

966
01:11:53,640 --> 01:11:56,680
<i>If you fuck up and</i>
<i>embarrass yourself in front of everyone,</i>

967
01:11:56,760 --> 01:11:58,880
<i>I'll stay on the sinking ship with you.</i>

968
01:11:59,600 --> 01:12:01,960
<i>We'll fuck up together. Okay?</i>

969
01:12:02,040 --> 01:12:06,080
<i>I'm so lucky that I've been</i>
<i>giving it my all just to love you.</i>
